682@implementation WebRootLayer
683
684- (void)renderInContext:(CGContextRef)graphicsContext
685{
686 // AppKit calls -[CALayer renderInContext:] to render layer-backed views
687 // into bitmap contexts, but renderInContext: doesn't capture mask layers
688 // (<rdar://problem/9539526>), so we can't rely on it. Since our layer
689 // contents will have already been rendered by drawRect:, we can safely make
690 // this a NOOP.
691}

693@end

695// if YES, do the standard NSView hit test (which can't give the right result when HTML overlaps a view)
696static BOOL forceNSViewHitTest;
697
698// if YES, do the "top WebHTMLView" hit test (which we'd like to do all the time but can't because of Java requirements [see bug 4349721])
699static BOOL forceWebHTMLViewHitTest;

703static bool needsCursorRectsSupportAtPoint(NSWindow* window, NSPoint point)
704{
705 forceNSViewHitTest = YES;
706 NSView* view = [window._borderView hitTest:point];
707 forceNSViewHitTest = NO;
708
709 // WebHTMLView doesn't use cursor rects.
710 if ([view isKindOfClass:[WebHTMLView class]])
711 return false;
712
713#if ENABLE(NETSCAPE_PLUGIN_API)
714 // Neither do NPAPI plug-ins.
715 if ([view isKindOfClass:[WebBaseNetscapePluginView class]])
716 return false;
717#endif
718
719 // Non-Web content, WebPDFView, and WebKit plug-ins use normal cursor handling.
720 return true;
721}

751@interface NSView (WebSetNeedsDisplayInRect)
752- (void)_web_setNeedsDisplayInRect:(NSRect)invalidRect;
753@end
754
755@implementation NSView (WebSetNeedsDisplayInRect)
756
757- (void)_web_setNeedsDisplayInRect:(NSRect)invalidRect
758{
759 // Note that we call method_exchangeImplementations below, so any calls
760 // to _web_setNeedsDisplayInRect: will actually call -[NSView setNeedsDisplayInRect:].
761
762 if (![NSThread isMainThread] || ![self _drawnByAncestor]) {
763 [self _web_setNeedsDisplayInRect:invalidRect];
764 return;
765 }
766
767 static Class webFrameViewClass = [WebFrameView class];
768 WebFrameView *enclosingWebFrameView = (WebFrameView *)self;
769 while (enclosingWebFrameView && ![enclosingWebFrameView isKindOfClass:webFrameViewClass])
770 enclosingWebFrameView = (WebFrameView *)[enclosingWebFrameView superview];
771
772 if (!enclosingWebFrameView) {
773 [self _web_setNeedsDisplayInRect:invalidRect];
774 return;
775 }
776
777 auto* coreFrame = core([enclosingWebFrameView webFrame]);
778 auto* frameView = coreFrame ? coreFrame->view() : 0;
779 if (!frameView || !frameView->isEnclosedInCompositingLayer()) {
780 [self _web_setNeedsDisplayInRect:invalidRect];
781 return;
782 }
783
784 NSRect invalidRectInWebFrameViewCoordinates = [enclosingWebFrameView convertRect:invalidRect fromView:self];
785 WebCore::IntRect invalidRectInFrameViewCoordinates(invalidRectInWebFrameViewCoordinates);
786 if (![enclosingWebFrameView isFlipped])
787 invalidRectInFrameViewCoordinates.setY(frameView->frameRect().size().height() - invalidRectInFrameViewCoordinates.maxY());
788
789 frameView->invalidateRect(invalidRectInFrameViewCoordinates);
790}

1130- (DOMDocumentFragment *)_documentFragmentWithPaths:(NSArray *)paths
1131{

1133

1136 // be pasted as visible text.

1138 [textNodes addObject:[[[self _frame] DOMDocument] createTextNode:url]];
1139 }

1145+ (NSArray *)_excludedElementsForAttributedStringConversion
1146{
1147 auto elements = adoptNS([[NSMutableArray alloc] initWithObjects:
1148 // Omit style since we want style to be inline so the fragment can be easily inserted.
1149 @"style",
1150 // Omit xml so the result is not XHTML.
1151 @"xml",
1152 // Omit tags that will get stripped when converted to a fragment anyway.
1153 @"doctype", @"html", @"head", @"body",
1154 // Omit deprecated tags.
1155 @"applet", @"basefont", @"center", @"dir", @"font", @"menu", @"s", @"strike", @"u",
1156 // Omit object so no file attachments are part of the fragment.
1157#if !ENABLE(ATTACHMENT_ELEMENT)
1158 // Omit object so no file attachments are part of the fragment.
1159 @"object",
1160#endif
1161 nil]);
1162
1163#if ENABLE(ATTACHMENT_ELEMENT)
1164 if (!WebCore::RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().attachmentElementEnabled())
1165 [elements addObject:@"object"];
1166#endif
1167
1168 return elements.autorelease();

1171- (DOMDocumentFragment *)_documentFragmentFromPasteboard:(NSPasteboard *)pasteboard inContext:(DOMRange *)context allowPlainText:(BOOL)allowPlainText
1172{
1173 using namespace WebCore;
1174 NSArray *types = [pasteboard types];
1175 DOMDocumentFragment *fragment = nil;
1176
1177 if ([types containsObject:WebArchivePboardType] && (fragment = [self _documentFragmentFromPasteboard:pasteboard forType:WebArchivePboardType inContext:context subresources:0]))
1178 return fragment;
1179
1180 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyFilenamesPasteboardType()] && (fragment = [self _documentFragmentFromPasteboard:pasteboard forType:WebCore::legacyFilenamesPasteboardType() inContext:context subresources:0]))
1181 return fragment;
1182
1183 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyHTMLPasteboardType()] && (fragment = [self _documentFragmentFromPasteboard:pasteboard forType:WebCore::legacyHTMLPasteboardType() inContext:context subresources:0]))
1184 return fragment;
1185
1186 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyRTFDPasteboardType()] && (fragment = [self _documentFragmentFromPasteboard:pasteboard forType:WebCore::legacyRTFDPasteboardType() inContext:context subresources:0]))
1187 return fragment;
1188
1189 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyRTFPasteboardType()] && (fragment = [self _documentFragmentFromPasteboard:pasteboard forType:WebCore::legacyRTFPasteboardType() inContext:context subresources:0]))
1190 return fragment;
1191
1192 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyTIFFPasteboardType()] && (fragment = [self _documentFragmentFromPasteboard:pasteboard forType:WebCore::legacyTIFFPasteboardType() inContext:context subresources:0]))
1193 return fragment;
1194
1195 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyPDFPasteboardType()] && (fragment = [self _documentFragmentFromPasteboard:pasteboard forType:WebCore::legacyPDFPasteboardType() inContext:context subresources:0]))
1196 return fragment;
1197
1198ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_BEGIN
1199 if ([types containsObject:(NSString *)kUTTypePNG] && (fragment = [self _documentFragmentFromPasteboard:pasteboard forType:(NSString *)kUTTypePNG inContext:context subresources:0]))
1200 return fragment;
1201ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_END
1202
1203 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyURLPasteboardType()] && (fragment = [self _documentFragmentFromPasteboard:pasteboard forType:WebCore::legacyURLPasteboardType() inContext:context subresources:0]))
1204 return fragment;
1205
1206 if (allowPlainText && [types containsObject:WebCore::legacyStringPasteboardType()] && (fragment = [self _documentFragmentFromPasteboard:pasteboard forType:WebCore::legacyStringPasteboardType() inContext:context subresources:0]))
1207 return fragment;
1208
1209 return nil;
1210}

1212- (NSString *)_plainTextFromPasteboard:(NSPasteboard *)pasteboard
1213{
1214 NSArray *types = [pasteboard types];
1215
1216 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyStringPasteboardType()])
1217 return [[pasteboard stringForType:WebCore::legacyStringPasteboardType()] precomposedStringWithCanonicalMapping];
1218
1219 RetainPtr<NSAttributedString> attributedString;
1220 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyRTFDPasteboardType()])
1221 attributedString = adoptNS([[NSAttributedString alloc] initWithRTFD:[pasteboard dataForType:WebCore::legacyRTFDPasteboardType()] documentAttributes:NULL]);
1222 if (attributedString == nil && [types containsObject:WebCore::legacyRTFPasteboardType()])
1223 attributedString = adoptNS([[NSAttributedString alloc] initWithRTF:[pasteboard dataForType:WebCore::legacyRTFPasteboardType()] documentAttributes:NULL]);
1224 if (attributedString)
1225 return adoptNS([[attributedString string] copy]).autorelease();
1226
1227 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyFilenamesPasteboardType()]) {
1228 if (NSString *string = [[pasteboard propertyListForType:WebCore::legacyFilenamesPasteboardType()] componentsJoinedByString:@"\n"])
1229 return string;
1230 }
1231
1232 if (NSURL *URL = [NSURL URLFromPasteboard:pasteboard]) {
1233 NSString *string = [URL _web_userVisibleString];
1234 if ([string length])
1235 return string;
1236 }
1237
1238 return nil;
1239}

1241- (void)_pasteWithPasteboard:(NSPasteboard *)pasteboard allowPlainText:(BOOL)allowPlainText
1242{
1243 auto webView = retainPtr([self _webView]);
1244 [webView _setInsertionPasteboard:pasteboard];
1245
1246 DOMRange *range = [self _selectedRange];
1247 auto* coreFrame = core([self _frame]);
1248
1249 DOMDocumentFragment *fragment = [self _documentFragmentFromPasteboard:pasteboard inContext:range allowPlainText:allowPlainText];
1250 if (fragment && [self _shouldInsertFragment:fragment replacingDOMRange:range givenAction:WebViewInsertActionPasted])
1251 coreFrame->editor().pasteAsFragment(*core(fragment), [self _canSmartReplaceWithPasteboard:pasteboard], false);
1252
1253 [webView _setInsertionPasteboard:nil];
1254}

1257{
1258 auto webView = retainPtr([self _webView]);
1259 [webView _setInsertionPasteboard:pasteboard];
1260
1261 NSString *text = [self _plainTextFromPasteboard:pasteboard];
1262 if ([self _shouldReplaceSelectionWithText:text givenAction:WebViewInsertActionPasted])
1263 [[self _frame] _replaceSelectionWithText:text selectReplacement:NO smartReplace:[self _canSmartReplaceWithPasteboard:pasteboard]];
1264
1265 [webView _setInsertionPasteboard:nil];
1266}

1289- (void)_removeSuperviewObservers
1290{
1291 if (!_private || !_private->observingSuperviewNotifications)
1292 return;
1293
1294 NSView *superview = [self superview];
1295 if (!superview || ![self window])
1296 return;
1297
1298 NSNotificationCenter *notificationCenter = [NSNotificationCenter defaultCenter];
1299 [notificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSViewFrameDidChangeNotification object:superview];
1300 [notificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSViewBoundsDidChangeNotification object:superview];
1301
1302 _private->observingSuperviewNotifications = false;
1303}

1305- (void)_removeWindowObservers
1306{
1307 if (!_private->observingWindowNotifications)
1308 return;
1309
1310 NSWindow *window = [self window];
1311 if (!window)
1312 return;
1313
1314 NSNotificationCenter *notificationCenter = [NSNotificationCenter defaultCenter];
1315 [notificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSWindowDidBecomeKeyNotification object:nil];
1316 [notificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSWindowDidResignKeyNotification object:nil];
1317 [notificationCenter removeObserver:self name:NSWindowWillCloseNotification object:window];
1318
1319 _private->observingWindowNotifications = false;
1320}

1352- (void)_writeSelectionWithPasteboardTypes:(NSArray *)types toPasteboard:(NSPasteboard *)pasteboard cachedAttributedString:(NSAttributedString *)attributedString
1353{
1354 // Put HTML on the pasteboard.
1355 if ([types containsObject:WebArchivePboardType]) {
1356 if (auto coreArchive = WebCore::LegacyWebArchive::createFromSelection(core([self _frame]))) {
1357 if (RetainPtr<CFDataRef> data = coreArchive ? coreArchive->rawDataRepresentation() : 0)
1358 [pasteboard setData:(__bridge NSData *)data.get() forType:WebArchivePboardType];
1359 }
1360 }
1361
1362 // Put the attributed string on the pasteboard (RTF/RTFD format).
1363 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyRTFDPasteboardType()]) {
1364 if (attributedString == nil) {
1365 attributedString = [self selectedAttributedString];
1366 }
1367 NSData *RTFDData = [attributedString RTFDFromRange:NSMakeRange(0, [attributedString length]) documentAttributes:@{ }];
1368 [pasteboard setData:RTFDData forType:WebCore::legacyRTFDPasteboardType()];
1369 }
1370 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyRTFPasteboardType()]) {
1371 if (!attributedString)
1372 attributedString = [self selectedAttributedString];
1373 if ([attributedString containsAttachments])
1374 attributedString = WebCore::attributedStringByStrippingAttachmentCharacters(attributedString);
1375 NSData *RTFData = [attributedString RTFFromRange:NSMakeRange(0, [attributedString length]) documentAttributes:@{ }];
1376 [pasteboard setData:RTFData forType:WebCore::legacyRTFPasteboardType()];
1377 }
1378
1379 // Put plain string on the pasteboard.
1380 if ([types containsObject:WebCore::legacyStringPasteboardType()]) {
1381 // Map &nbsp; to a plain old space because this is better for source code, other browsers do it, and
1382 // because HTML forces content creators and editors to use this character any time they want two spaces in a row.
1383 [pasteboard setString:[[self selectedString] stringByReplacingOccurrencesOfString:@"\u00A0" withString:@" "] forType:WebCore::legacyStringPasteboardType()];
1384 }

1386 if ([self _canSmartCopyOrDelete] && [types containsObject:WebSmartPastePboardType])
1387 [pasteboard setData:nil forType:WebSmartPastePboardType];

1602// Don't let AppKit even draw subviews. We take care of that.
1603- (void)_recursiveDisplayRectIfNeededIgnoringOpacity:(NSRect)rect isVisibleRect:(BOOL)isVisibleRect rectIsVisibleRectForView:(NSView *)visibleView topView:(BOOL)topView
1604{
1605 // This helps when we print as part of a larger print process.
1606 // If the WebHTMLView itself is what we're printing, then we will never have to do this.
1607 BOOL wasInPrintingMode = _private->printing;
1608 BOOL isPrinting = ![NSGraphicsContext currentContextDrawingToScreen];
1609 if (isPrinting) {
1610 if (!wasInPrintingMode)
1611 [self _web_setPrintingModeRecursive];
1612 else
1613 [self _web_updateLayoutAndStyleIfNeededRecursive];
1614 } else if (wasInPrintingMode)
1615 [self _web_clearPrintingModeRecursive];
1616
1617 // There are known cases where -viewWillDraw is not called on all views being drawn.
1618 // See <rdar://problem/6964278> for example. Performing layout at this point prevents us from
1619 // trying to paint without layout (which WebCore now refuses to do, instead bailing out without
1620 // drawing at all), but we may still fail to update any regions dirtied by the layout which are
1621 // not already dirty.
1622 if ([self _needsLayout]) {
1623 NSInteger rectCount;
1624 [self getRectsBeingDrawn:0 count:&rectCount];
1625 if (rectCount) {
1626 LOG_ERROR("View needs layout. Either -viewWillDraw wasn't called or layout was invalidated during the display operation. Performing layout now.");
1627 [self _web_updateLayoutAndStyleIfNeededRecursive];
1628 }
1629 }
1630
1631 [self _setAsideSubviews];
1632 [super _recursiveDisplayRectIfNeededIgnoringOpacity:rect isVisibleRect:isVisibleRect rectIsVisibleRectForView:visibleView topView:topView];
1633 [self _restoreSubviews];
1634
1635 if (wasInPrintingMode != isPrinting) {
1636 if (wasInPrintingMode)
1637 [self _web_setPrintingModeRecursive];
1638 else
1639 [self _web_clearPrintingModeRecursive];
1640 }
1641}

1704- (NSView *)hitTest:(NSPoint)point
1705{
1706 // WebHTMLView objects handle all events for objects inside them.
1707 // To get those events, we prevent hit testing from AppKit.
1708
1709 // But there are three exceptions to this:
1710 // 1) For right mouse clicks and control clicks we don't yet have an implementation
1711 // that works for nested views, so we let the hit testing go through the
1712 // standard NSView code path (needs to be fixed, see bug 4361618).
1713 // 2) Java depends on doing a hit test inside it's mouse moved handling,
1714 // so we let the hit testing go through the standard NSView code path
1715 // when the current event is a mouse move (except when we are calling
1716 // from _updateMouseoverWithEvent, so we have to use a global,
1717 // forceWebHTMLViewHitTest, for that)
1718 // 3) The acceptsFirstMouse: and shouldDelayWindowOrderingForEvent: methods
1719 // both need to figure out which view to check with inside the WebHTMLView.
1720 // They use a global to change the behavior of hitTest: so they can get the
1721 // right view. The global is forceNSViewHitTest and the method they use to
1722 // do the hit testing is _hitViewForEvent:. (But this does not work correctly
1723 // when there is HTML overlapping the view, see bug 4361626)
1724 // 4) NSAccessibilityHitTest relies on this for checking the cursor position.
1725 // Our check for that is whether the event is NSFlagsChanged. This works
1726 // for VoiceOver's Control-Option-F5 command (move focus to item under cursor)
1727 // and Dictionary's Command-Control-D (open dictionary popup for item under cursor).
1728 // This is of course a hack.
1729
1730 if (_private->closed)
1731 return nil;
1732
1733#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1734 BOOL captureHitsOnSubviews;
1735 if (forceNSViewHitTest)
1736 captureHitsOnSubviews = NO;
1737 else if (forceWebHTMLViewHitTest)
1738 captureHitsOnSubviews = YES;
1739 else {
1740 // FIXME: Why doesn't this include mouse entered/exited events, or other mouse button events?
1741 NSEvent *event = [[self window] currentEvent];
1742 captureHitsOnSubviews = !([event type] == NSEventTypeMouseMoved
1743 || [event type] == NSEventTypeRightMouseDown
1744 || ([event type] == NSEventTypeLeftMouseDown && [event modifierFlags] & NSEventModifierFlagControl)
1745 || [event type] == NSEventTypeFlagsChanged
1746 || isQuickLookEvent(event));
1747 }
1748
1749 if (!captureHitsOnSubviews) {
1750 NSView* hitView = [super hitTest:point];
1751 if (_private && hitView == _private->layerHostingView)
1752 hitView = self;
1753 return hitView;
1754 }
1755#endif // !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1756
1757 if ([[self superview] mouse:point inRect:[self frame]])
1758 return self;
1759 return nil;
1760}

1887static bool mouseEventIsPartOfClickOrDrag(NSEvent *event)
1888{
1889 switch ([event type]) {
1890 case NSEventTypeLeftMouseDown:
1891 case NSEventTypeLeftMouseUp:
1892 case NSEventTypeLeftMouseDragged:
1893 case NSEventTypeRightMouseDown:
1894 case NSEventTypeRightMouseUp:
1895 case NSEventTypeRightMouseDragged:
1896 case NSEventTypeOtherMouseDown:
1897 case NSEventTypeOtherMouseUp:
1898 case NSEventTypeOtherMouseDragged:
1899 return true;
1900 default:
1901 return false;
1902 }

1905- (void)_updateMouseoverWithEvent:(NSEvent *)event
1906{
1907 if (_private->closed)
1908 return;
1909
1910 NSView *contentView = [[event window] contentView];
1911 NSPoint locationForHitTest = [[contentView superview] convertPoint:[event locationInWindow] fromView:nil];
1912
1913 forceWebHTMLViewHitTest = YES;
1914 NSView *hitView = [contentView hitTest:locationForHitTest];
1915 forceWebHTMLViewHitTest = NO;
1916
1917 auto view = retainPtr(dynamic_objc_cast<WebHTMLView>(hitView));
1918 if (lastHitView != view && lastHitView && [lastHitView _frame]) {
1919 // If we are moving out of a view (or frame), let's pretend the mouse moved
1920 // all the way out of that view. But we have to account for scrolling, because
1921 // WebCore doesn't understand our clipping.
1922 NSRect visibleRect = [[[[lastHitView _frame] frameView] _scrollView] documentVisibleRect];
1923 float yScroll = visibleRect.origin.y;
1924 float xScroll = visibleRect.origin.x;
1925
1926 NSEvent *event = [NSEvent mouseEventWithType:NSEventTypeMouseMoved
1927 location:NSMakePoint(-1 - xScroll, -1 - yScroll)
1928 modifierFlags:[[NSApp currentEvent] modifierFlags]
1929 timestamp:[NSDate timeIntervalSinceReferenceDate]
1930 windowNumber:[[view window] windowNumber]
1931 context:nullptr
1932 eventNumber:0 clickCount:0 pressure:0];
1933
1934 if (auto* lastHitCoreFrame = core([lastHitView _frame]))
1935 lastHitCoreFrame->eventHandler().mouseMoved(event, [[self _webView] _pressureEvent]);
1936 }
1937
1938 lastHitView = view.get();
1939
1940 if (view) {
1941 if (auto* coreFrame = core([view _frame])) {
1942 // We need to do a full, normal hit test during this mouse event if the page is active or if a mouse
1943 // button is currently pressed. It is possible that neither of those things will be true on Lion and
1944 // newer when legacy scrollbars are enabled, because then WebKit receives mouse events all the time.
1945 // If it is one of those cases where the page is not active and the mouse is not pressed, then we can
1946 // fire a much more restricted and efficient scrollbars-only version of the event.
1947
1948 if ([[self window] isKeyWindow] || mouseEventIsPartOfClickOrDrag(event))
1949 coreFrame->eventHandler().mouseMoved(event, [[self _webView] _pressureEvent]);
1950 else {
1951 [self removeAllToolTips];
1952 coreFrame->eventHandler().passMouseMovedEventToScrollbars(event, [[self _webView] _pressureEvent]);
1953 }
1954 }
1955 }
1956}

2509- (CGFloat)_adjustedBottomOfPageWithTop:(CGFloat)top bottom:(CGFloat)bottom limit:(CGFloat)bottomLimit
2510{
2511 auto* frame = core([self _frame]);
2512 if (!frame)
2513 return bottom;
2514
2515 auto* view = frame->view();
2516 if (!view)
2517 return bottom;
2518
2519 float newBottom;
2520 view->adjustPageHeightDeprecated(&newBottom, top, bottom, bottomLimit);
2521
2522 // If the new bottom is equal to the old bottom (when both are treated as floats), we just return the original
2523 // bottom. This prevents rounding errors that can occur when converting newBottom to a double.
2524 if (WTF::areEssentiallyEqual(static_cast<float>(bottom), newBottom))
2525 return bottom;
2526 return newBottom;
2527}

2644typedef HashMap<SEL, String> SelectorNameMap;
2645
2646// Map selectors into Editor command names.
2647// This is not needed for any selectors that have the same name as the Editor command.
2648static const SelectorNameMap* createSelectorExceptionMap()
2649{
2650 SelectorNameMap* map = new HashMap<SEL, String>;
2651
2652 map->add(@selector(insertNewlineIgnoringFieldEditor:), "InsertNewline");
2653 map->add(@selector(insertParagraphSeparator:), "InsertNewline");
2654 map->add(@selector(insertTabIgnoringFieldEditor:), "InsertTab");
2655 map->add(@selector(pageDown:), "MovePageDown");
2656 map->add(@selector(pageDownAndModifySelection:), "MovePageDownAndModifySelection");
2657 map->add(@selector(pageUp:), "MovePageUp");
2658 map->add(@selector(pageUpAndModifySelection:), "MovePageUpAndModifySelection");
2659
2660 return map;
2661}
2662
2663static String commandNameForSelector(SEL selector)
2664{
2665 // Check the exception map first.
2666 static const SelectorNameMap* exceptionMap = createSelectorExceptionMap();
2667 SelectorNameMap::const_iterator it = exceptionMap->find(selector);
2668 if (it != exceptionMap->end())
2669 return it->value;
2670
2671 // Remove the trailing colon.
2672 // No need to capitalize the command name since Editor command names are
2673 // not case sensitive.
2674 const char* selectorName = sel_getName(selector);
2675 size_t selectorNameLength = strlen(selectorName);
2676 if (selectorNameLength < 2 || selectorName[selectorNameLength - 1] != ':')
2677 return String();
2678 return String(selectorName, selectorNameLength - 1);
2679}

3087- (BOOL)acceptsFirstResponder
3088{
3089 // Don't accept first responder when we first click on this view.
3090 // We have to pass the event down through WebCore first to be sure we don't hit a subview.
3091 // Do accept first responder at any other time, for example from keyboard events,
3092 // or from calls back from WebCore once we begin mouse-down event handling.
3093#if PLATFORM(MAC)
3094 WebEvent *event = [NSApp currentEvent];
3095#else
3096 WebEvent *event = [WAKWindow currentEvent];
3097#endif
3098 if (event && event.type == WebEventMouseDown
3099 && !_private->handlingMouseDownEvent
3100 && NSPointInRect([event locationInWindow], [self convertRect:[self visibleRect] toView:nil]))
3101 return NO;
3102 return YES;
3103}

3105- (BOOL)maintainsInactiveSelection
3106{
3107#if USE(UIKIT_EDITING)
3108 // We want to maintain an inactive selection, when in editable content.
3109 if ([[self _webView] maintainsInactiveSelection])
3110 return YES;
3111
3112 if ([[self window] _newFirstResponderAfterResigning] == self)
3113 return YES;
3114
3115 auto* coreFrame = core([self _frame]);
3116 return coreFrame && coreFrame->selection().selection().isContentEditable();
3117#else
3118 // This method helps to determine whether the WebHTMLView should maintain
3119 // an inactive selection when it's not first responder.
3120 // Traditionally, these views have not maintained such selections,
3121 // clearing them when the view was not first responder. However,
3122 // to fix bugs like this one:
3123 // <rdar://problem/3672088>: "Editable WebViews should maintain a selection even
3124 // when they're not firstResponder"
3125 // it was decided to add a switch to act more like an NSTextView.
3126
3127 if ([[self _webView] maintainsInactiveSelection])
3128 return YES;
3129
3130 // Predict the case where we are losing first responder status only to
3131 // gain it back again. Want to keep the selection in that case.
3132 id nextResponder = [[self window] _newFirstResponderAfterResigning];
3133 if ([nextResponder isKindOfClass:[NSScrollView class]]) {
3134 id contentView = [nextResponder contentView];
3135 if (contentView)

3412static RetainPtr<NSArray> fixMenusToSendToOldClients(NSMutableArray *defaultMenuItems)
3413{
3414 auto savedItems = adoptNS([[NSMutableArray alloc] init]);
3415
3416 unsigned defaultItemsCount = [defaultMenuItems count];
3417
3418 if (isPreInspectElementTagClient() && defaultItemsCount >= 2) {
3419 NSMenuItem *secondToLastItem = [defaultMenuItems objectAtIndex:defaultItemsCount - 2];
3420 NSMenuItem *lastItem = [defaultMenuItems objectAtIndex:defaultItemsCount - 1];
3421
3422 if ([secondToLastItem isSeparatorItem] && [lastItem tag] == WebMenuItemTagInspectElement) {
3423 savedItems = adoptNS([[NSMutableArray alloc] initWithCapacity:2]);
3424 [savedItems addObject:secondToLastItem];
3425 [savedItems addObject:lastItem];
3426
3427 [defaultMenuItems removeObject:secondToLastItem];
3428 [defaultMenuItems removeObject:lastItem];
3429 defaultItemsCount -= 2;
3430 }
3431 }
3432
3433 BOOL preVersion3Client = isPreVersion3Client();
3434 if (!preVersion3Client)
3435 return savedItems;
3436
3437 for (NSMenuItem *item in defaultMenuItems) {
3438 int tag = item.tag;
3439 int oldStyleTag = tag;
3440
3441 if (tag >= WEBMENUITEMTAG_WEBKIT_3_0_SPI_START) {
3442 // Change all editing-related SPI tags listed in WebUIDelegatePrivate.h to WebMenuItemTagOther
3443 // to match our old WebKit context menu behavior.
3444 oldStyleTag = WebMenuItemTagOther;
3445 } else {
3446 // All items are expected to have useful tags coming into this method.
3447 ASSERT(tag != WebMenuItemTagOther);
3448
3449 // Use the pre-3.0 tags for the few items that changed tags as they moved from SPI to API. We
3450 // do this only for old clients; new Mail already expects the new symbols in this case.
3451 if (preVersion3Client) {
3452 switch (tag) {
3453 case WebMenuItemTagSearchInSpotlight:
3454 oldStyleTag = OldWebMenuItemTagSearchInSpotlight;
3455 break;
3456 case WebMenuItemTagSearchWeb:
3457 oldStyleTag = OldWebMenuItemTagSearchWeb;
3458 break;
3459 case WebMenuItemTagLookUpInDictionary:
3460 oldStyleTag = OldWebMenuItemTagLookUpInDictionary;
3461 break;
3462 default:
3463 break;
3464 }
3465 }
3466 }
3467
3468 item.tag = oldStyleTag;
3469 }
3470
3471 return savedItems;

3634{

3641 return createShareMenuItem(hitTestResult);

3644 case WebCore::ActionType:
3645 case WebCore::CheckableActionType: {

3655 }

3657 case WebCore::SeparatorType:

3680static RetainPtr<NSArray> customMenuFromDefaultItems(WebView *webView, const WebCore::ContextMenu& defaultMenu)
3681{
3682 const auto& hitTestResult = webView.page->contextMenuController().hitTestResult();
3683 bool isPopover = webView.window._childWindowOrderingPriority == NSWindowChildOrderingPriorityPopover;
3684 bool isLookupDisabled = [NSUserDefaults.standardUserDefaults boolForKey:@"LULookupDisabled"];

3722- (NSMenu *)menuForEvent:(NSEvent *)event
3723{
3724 // There's a chance that if we run a nested event loop the event will be released.
3725 // Retaining and then autoreleasing prevents that from causing a problem later here or
3726 // inside AppKit code.
3727 retainPtr(event).autorelease();
3728
3729 [_private->completionController endRevertingChange:NO moveLeft:NO];
3730
3731 RefPtr<WebCore::Frame> coreFrame = core([self _frame]);
3732 if (!coreFrame)
3733 return nil;
3734
3735 auto* page = coreFrame->page();
3736 if (!page)
3737 return nil;
3738
3739 // Match behavior of other browsers by sending a mousedown event for right clicks.
3740 _private->handlingMouseDownEvent = YES;
3741 page->contextMenuController().clearContextMenu();
3742 coreFrame->eventHandler().mouseDown(event, [[self _webView] _pressureEvent]);
3743 BOOL handledEvent = coreFrame->eventHandler().sendContextMenuEvent(WebCore::PlatformEventFactory::createPlatformMouseEvent(event, [[self _webView] _pressureEvent], page->chrome().platformPageClient()));
3744 _private->handlingMouseDownEvent = NO;
3745
3746 if (!handledEvent)
3747 return nil;
3748
3749 // Re-get page, since it might have gone away during event handling.
3750 page = coreFrame->page();
3751 if (!page)
3752 return nil;
3753
3754 auto* contextMenu = page->contextMenuController().contextMenu();
3755 if (!contextMenu)

3921- (void)drawRect:(NSRect)rect
3922{
3923 LOG(View, "%@ drawing", self);
3924
3925 TraceScope scope(WebHTMLViewPaintStart, WebHTMLViewPaintEnd);
3926
3927#if PLATFORM(MAC)
3928 const NSRect *rects;
3929 NSInteger count;
3930 [self getRectsBeingDrawn:&rects count:&count];
3931
3932 BOOL subviewsWereSetAside = _private->subviewsSetAside;
3933 if (subviewsWereSetAside)
3934 [self _restoreSubviews];
3935#endif
3936
3937#ifdef LOG_TIMES
3938 double start = CFAbsoluteTimeGetCurrent();
3939#endif
3940
3941#if PLATFORM(MAC)
3942 // If count == 0 here, use the rect passed in for drawing. This is a workaround for:
3943 // <rdar://problem/3908282> REGRESSION (Mail): No drag image dragging selected text in Blot and Mail
3944 // The reason for the workaround is that this method is called explicitly from the code
3945 // to generate a drag image, and at that time, getRectsBeingDrawn:count: will return a zero count.
3946 const int cRectThreshold = 10;
3947 const float cWastedSpaceThreshold = 0.75f;
3948 BOOL useUnionedRect = (count <= 1) || (count > cRectThreshold);
3949 if (!useUnionedRect) {
3950 // Attempt to guess whether or not we should use the unioned rect or the individual rects.
3951 // We do this by computing the percentage of "wasted space" in the union. If that wasted space
3952 // is too large, then we will do individual rect painting instead.
3953 float unionPixels = (rect.size.width * rect.size.height);
3954 float singlePixels = 0;
3955 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i)
3956 singlePixels += rects[i].size.width * rects[i].size.height;
3957 float wastedSpace = 1 - (singlePixels / unionPixels);
3958 if (wastedSpace <= cWastedSpaceThreshold)
3959 useUnionedRect = YES;
3960 }
3961
3962 if (useUnionedRect)
3963 [self drawSingleRect:rect];
3964 else {
3965 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i)
3966 [self drawSingleRect:rects[i]];
3967 }
3968#else
3969 [self drawSingleRect:rect];
3970#endif
3971
3972#ifdef LOG_TIMES
3973 double thisTime = CFAbsoluteTimeGetCurrent() - start;
3974 LOG(Timing, "%s draw seconds = %f", widget->part()->baseURL().URL().latin1(), thisTime);
3975#endif
3976
3977#if PLATFORM(MAC)
3978 if (subviewsWereSetAside)
3979 [self _setAsideSubviews];
3980#endif
3981
3982 WebView *webView = [self _webView];
3983
3984#if PLATFORM(MAC)
3985 // Only do the synchronization dance if we're drawing into the window, otherwise
3986 // we risk disabling screen updates when no flush is pending.
3987 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_BEGIN
3988 if ([NSGraphicsContext currentContext] == [[self window] graphicsContext] && [webView _needsOneShotDrawingSynchronization]) {
3989 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_END
3990 // Disable screen updates to minimize the chances of the race between the CA
3991 // display link and AppKit drawing causing flashes.
3992 [[self window] disableScreenUpdatesUntilFlush];
3993
3994 // Make sure any layer changes that happened as a result of layout
3995 // via -viewWillDraw are committed.
3996 [CATransaction flush];
3997 [webView _setNeedsOneShotDrawingSynchronization:NO];
3998 }
3999#endif
4000
4001 if (webView)
4002 CallUIDelegate(webView, @selector(webView:didDrawFrame:), [self _frame]);
4003}

4184#if PLATFORM(MAC)

4386 if (!wrapper) {
4387 ASSERT(![self _webView] || [self _isTopHTMLView]);
4388 auto* page = core([self _webView]);
4389
4390 //If a load occurs midway through a drag, the view may be detached, which gives
4391 //us no ability to get to the original Page, so we cannot access any drag state
4392 //FIXME: is there a way to recover?
4393 if (!page)
4394 return nil;
4395
4396 const URL& imageURL = page->dragController().draggingImageURL();
4397 if (!imageURL.isEmpty())
4398 draggingElementURL = imageURL;
4399
4400 wrapper = [[self _dataSource] _fileWrapperForURL:draggingElementURL];
4401 }
4402
4403 if (wrapper == nil) {
4404 LOG_ERROR("Failed to create image file.");
4405 return nil;
4406 }
4407
4408 // FIXME: Report an error if we fail to create a file.
4409 NSString *path = [[dropDestination path] stringByAppendingPathComponent:[wrapper preferredFilename]];
4410 path = [[NSFileManager defaultManager] _webkit_pathWithUniqueFilenameForPath:path];
4411 if (![wrapper writeToURL:[NSURL fileURLWithPath:path isDirectory:NO] options:NSFileWrapperWritingWithNameUpdating originalContentsURL:nil error:nullptr])
4412 LOG_ERROR("Failed to create image file via -[NSFileWrapper writeToURL:options:originalContentsURL:error:]");
4413
4414 if (draggingElementURL)
4415 [[NSFileManager defaultManager] _webkit_setMetadataURL:[draggingElementURL absoluteString] referrer:nil atPath:path];
4416
4417 return @[[path lastPathComponent]];
4418}

4783- (float)_scaleFactorForPrintOperation:(NSPrintOperation *)printOperation
4784{
4785 bool useViewWidth = true;
4786 auto* coreFrame = core([self _frame]);
4787 if (coreFrame) {
4788 auto* document = coreFrame->document();
4789 if (document && document->renderView())
4790 useViewWidth = document->renderView()->style().isHorizontalWritingMode();
4791 }
4792
4793 float viewLogicalWidth = useViewWidth ? NSWidth([self bounds]) : NSHeight([self bounds]);
4794 if (viewLogicalWidth < 1) {
4795 LOG_ERROR("%@ has no logical width when printing", self);
4796 return 1.0f;
4797 }
4798
4799 float userScaleFactor = [printOperation _web_pageSetupScaleFactor];
4800 float maxShrinkToFitScaleFactor = 1.0f / _WebHTMLViewPrintingMaximumShrinkFactor;
4801 float shrinkToFitScaleFactor = (useViewWidth ? [printOperation _web_availablePaperWidth] : [printOperation _web_availablePaperHeight]) / viewLogicalWidth;
4802 return userScaleFactor * std::max(maxShrinkToFitScaleFactor, shrinkToFitScaleFactor);
4803}

4807// if AppKit makes it SPI/API.
4808- (CGFloat)_provideTotalScaleFactorForPrintOperation:(NSPrintOperation *)printOperation
4809{
4810 return [self _scaleFactorForPrintOperation:printOperation];

4828- (void)_delayedEndPrintMode:(NSPrintOperation *)initiatingOperation
4829{
4830 ASSERT_ARG(initiatingOperation, initiatingOperation != nil);
4831 NSPrintOperation *currentOperation = [NSPrintOperation currentOperation];
4832 if (initiatingOperation == currentOperation) {
4833 // The print operation is still underway. We don't expect this to ever happen, hence the assert, but we're
4834 // being extra paranoid here since the printing code is so fragile. Delay the cleanup
4835 // further.
4836 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4837 [self performSelector:@selector(_delayedEndPrintMode:) withObject:initiatingOperation afterDelay:0];
4838 } else if ([currentOperation view] == self) {
4839 // A new print job has started, but it is printing the same WebHTMLView again. We don't expect
4840 // this to ever happen, hence the assert, but we're being extra paranoid here since the printing code is so
4841 // fragile. Do nothing, because we don't want to break the print job currently in progress, and
4842 // the print job currently in progress is responsible for its own cleanup.
4843 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4844 } else {
4845 // The print job that kicked off this delayed call has finished, and this view is not being
4846 // printed again. We expect that no other print job has started. Since this delayed call wasn't
4847 // cancelled, beginDocument and endDocument must not have been called, and we need to clean up
4848 // the print mode here.
4849 ASSERT(currentOperation == nil);
4850 [self _endPrintModeAndRestoreWindowAutodisplay];
4851 }
4852}

4854// Return the number of pages available for printing
4855- (BOOL)knowsPageRange:(NSRangePointer)range
4856{
4857 // Must do this explicit display here, because otherwise the view might redisplay while the print
4858 // sheet was up, using printer fonts (and looking different).
4859 [self displayIfNeeded];
4860 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_BEGIN
4861 [[self window] setAutodisplay:NO];
4862 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_END
4863
4864 [[self _webView] _adjustPrintingMarginsForHeaderAndFooter];
4865 NSPrintOperation *printOperation = [NSPrintOperation currentOperation];
4866 if (![self _beginPrintModeWithPageWidth:[printOperation _web_availablePaperWidth] height:[printOperation _web_availablePaperHeight] shrinkToFit:YES])
4867 return NO;
4868
4869 // Certain types of errors, including invalid page ranges, can cause beginDocument and
4870 // endDocument to be skipped after we've put ourselves in print mode (see 4145905). In those cases
4871 // we need to get out of print mode without relying on any more callbacks from the printing mechanism.
4872 // If we get as far as beginDocument without trouble, then this delayed request will be cancelled.
4873 // If not cancelled, this delayed call will be invoked in the next pass through the main event loop,
4874 // which is after beginDocument and endDocument would be called.
4875 [self performSelector:@selector(_delayedEndPrintMode:) withObject:printOperation afterDelay:0];
4876
4877 // There is a theoretical chance that someone could do some drawing between here and endDocument,
4878 // if something caused setNeedsDisplay after this point. If so, it's not a big tragedy, because
4879 // you'd simply see the printer fonts on screen. As of this writing, this does not happen with Safari.
4880
4881 range->location = 1;
4882 float totalScaleFactor = [self _scaleFactorForPrintOperation:printOperation];
4883 float userScaleFactor = [printOperation _web_pageSetupScaleFactor];
4884 float fullPageWidth = floorf([printOperation _web_availablePaperWidth] / totalScaleFactor);
4885 float fullPageHeight = floorf([printOperation _web_availablePaperHeight] / totalScaleFactor);
4886 WebFrame *frame = [self _frame];
4887 NSArray *newPageRects = [frame _computePageRectsWithPrintScaleFactor:userScaleFactor pageSize:NSMakeSize(fullPageWidth, fullPageHeight)];
4888
4889 // AppKit gets all messed up if you give it a zero-length page count (see 3576334), so if we
4890 // hit that case we'll pass along a degenerate 1 pixel square to print. This will print
4891 // a blank page (with correct-looking header and footer if that option is on), which matches
4892 // the behavior of IE and Camino at least.
4893 if ([newPageRects count] == 0)
4894 newPageRects = @[[NSValue valueWithRect:NSMakeRect(0, 0, 1, 1)]];
4895
4896 _private->pageRects = newPageRects;
4897
4898 range->length = [_private->pageRects count];
4899
4900 return YES;
4901}

4906 return [[_private->pageRects objectAtIndex:page - 1] rectValue];

4940- (void)keyDown:(WebEvent *)event
4941{
4942#if PLATFORM(MAC)
4943 // There's a chance that responding to this event will run a nested event loop, and
4944 // fetching a new event might release the old one. Retaining and then autoreleasing
4945 // the current event prevents that from causing a problem inside WebKit or AppKit code.
4946 retainPtr(event).autorelease();
4947#endif
4948
4949 RetainPtr<WebHTMLView> selfProtector = self;
4950 BOOL eventWasSentToWebCore = (_private->keyDownEvent == event);
4951
4952 BOOL callSuper = NO;
4953
4954 _private->keyDownEvent = event;
4955
4956#if PLATFORM(MAC)
4957 BOOL completionPopupWasOpen = _private->completionController && [_private->completionController popupWindowIsOpen];
4958 auto* coreFrame = core([self _frame]);
4959 if (!eventWasSentToWebCore && coreFrame && coreFrame->eventHandler().keyEvent(event)) {
4960 // WebCore processed a key event, bail on any preexisting complete: UI
4961 if (completionPopupWasOpen)
4962 [_private->completionController endRevertingChange:YES moveLeft:NO];
4963 } else if (!_private->completionController || ![_private->completionController filterKeyDown:event]) {
4964 // Not consumed by complete: popup window
4965 [_private->completionController endRevertingChange:YES moveLeft:NO];
4966 callSuper = YES;
4967 }
4968#else
4969 auto* coreFrame = core([self _frame]);
4970 if (!eventWasSentToWebCore && coreFrame)
4971 coreFrame->eventHandler().keyEvent(event);
4972#endif
4973
4974 if (callSuper)
4975 [super keyDown:event];
4976 else {
4977#if PLATFORM(MAC)
4978 [NSCursor setHiddenUntilMouseMoves:YES];
4979#endif
4980 }

5119- (NSString *)_colorAsString:(NSColor *)color
5120{
5121 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_BEGIN
5122 NSColor *rgbColor = [color colorUsingColorSpaceName:NSDeviceRGBColorSpace];
5123 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_END
5124 // FIXME: If color is non-nil and rgbColor is nil, that means we got some kind
5125 // of fancy color that can't be converted to RGB. Changing that to "transparent"
5126 // might not be great, but it's probably OK.
5127 if (rgbColor == nil)
5128 return @"transparent";
5129 float r = [rgbColor redComponent];
5130 float g = [rgbColor greenComponent];
5131 float b = [rgbColor blueComponent];
5132 float a = [rgbColor alphaComponent];
5133 if (a == 0)
5134 return @"transparent";
5135 if (r == 0 && g == 0 && b == 0 && a == 1)
5136 return @"black";
5137 if (r == 1 && g == 1 && b == 1 && a == 1)
5138 return @"white";
5139 // FIXME: Lots more named colors. Maybe we could use the table in WebCore?
5140 if (a == 1)
5141 return [NSString stringWithFormat:@"rgb(%.0f,%.0f,%.0f)", r * 255, g * 255, b * 255];
5142 return [NSString stringWithFormat:@"rgba(%.0f,%.0f,%.0f,%f)", r * 255, g * 255, b * 255, a];
5143}

5145- (NSString *)_shadowAsString:(NSShadow *)shadow
5146{
5147 if (shadow == nil)
5148 return @"none";
5149 NSSize offset = [shadow shadowOffset];
5150 float blurRadius = [shadow shadowBlurRadius];
5151 if (offset.width == 0 && offset.height == 0 && blurRadius == 0)
5152 return @"none";
5153 NSColor *color = [shadow shadowColor];
5154 if (color == nil)
5155 return @"none";
5156 // FIXME: Handle non-integral values here?
5157 if (blurRadius == 0)
5158 return [NSString stringWithFormat:@"%@ %.0fpx %.0fpx", [self _colorAsString:color], offset.width, offset.height];
5159 return [NSString stringWithFormat:@"%@ %.0fpx %.0fpx %.0fpx", [self _colorAsString:color], offset.width, offset.height, blurRadius];

5162- (DOMCSSStyleDeclaration *)_styleFromFontAttributes:(NSDictionary *)dictionary
5163{
5164 DOMCSSStyleDeclaration *style = [self _emptyStyle];
5165
5166 NSColor *color = [dictionary objectForKey:NSBackgroundColorAttributeName];
5167 [style setBackgroundColor:[self _colorAsString:color]];
5168
5169 NSFont *font = [dictionary objectForKey:NSFontAttributeName];
5170 if (!font) {
5171 [style setFontFamily:@"Helvetica"];
5172 [style setFontSize:@"12px"];
5173 [style setFontWeight:@"normal"];
5174 [style setFontStyle:@"normal"];
5175 } else {
5176 NSFontManager *fm = [NSFontManager sharedFontManager];
5177 // FIXME: Need more sophisticated escaping code if we want to handle family names
5178 // with characters like single quote or backslash in their names.
5179 [style setFontFamily:[NSString stringWithFormat:@"'%@'", [font familyName]]];
5180 [style setFontSize:[NSString stringWithFormat:@"%0.fpx", [font pointSize]]];
5181 // FIXME: Map to the entire range of CSS weight values.
5182 if ([fm weightOfFont:font] >= MIN_BOLD_WEIGHT)
5183 [style setFontWeight:@"bold"];
5184 else
5185 [style setFontWeight:@"normal"];
5186 if ([fm traitsOfFont:font] & NSItalicFontMask)
5187 [style setFontStyle:@"italic"];
5188 else
5189 [style setFontStyle:@"normal"];
5190 }
5191
5192 color = [dictionary objectForKey:NSForegroundColorAttributeName];
5193 [style setColor:color ? [self _colorAsString:color] : (NSString *)@"black"];
5194
5195 NSShadow *shadow = [dictionary objectForKey:NSShadowAttributeName];
5196 [style setTextShadow:[self _shadowAsString:shadow]];
5197
5198 int strikethroughInt = [[dictionary objectForKey:NSStrikethroughStyleAttributeName] intValue];
5199
5200 int superscriptInt = [[dictionary objectForKey:NSSuperscriptAttributeName] intValue];
5201 if (superscriptInt > 0)
5202 [style setVerticalAlign:@"super"];
5203 else if (superscriptInt < 0)
5204 [style setVerticalAlign:@"sub"];
5205 else
5206 [style setVerticalAlign:@"baseline"];
5207 int underlineInt = [[dictionary objectForKey:NSUnderlineStyleAttributeName] intValue];
5208 // FIXME: Underline wins here if we have both (see bug 3790443).
5209 if (strikethroughInt == NSUnderlineStyleNone && underlineInt == NSUnderlineStyleNone)
5210 [style setProperty:@"-webkit-text-decorations-in-effect" value:@"none" priority:@""];
5211 else if (underlineInt == NSUnderlineStyleNone)
5212 [style setProperty:@"-webkit-text-decorations-in-effect" value:@"line-through" priority:@""];
5213 else
5214 [style setProperty:@"-webkit-text-decorations-in-effect" value:@"underline" priority:@""];
5215
5216 return style;
5217}

5234- (BOOL)_handleStyleKeyEquivalent:(NSEvent *)event
5235{
5236 WebView *webView = [self _webView];
5237 if (!webView)
5238 return NO;
5239
5240 if (![[webView preferences] respectStandardStyleKeyEquivalents])
5241 return NO;
5242
5243 if (![self _canEdit])
5244 return NO;

5246 if (([event modifierFlags] & NSEventModifierFlagDeviceIndependentFlagsMask) != NSEventModifierFlagCommand)
5247 return NO;
5248

5250 if ([string caseInsensitiveCompare:@"b"] == NSOrderedSame) {
5251 [self executeCoreCommandByName:"ToggleBold"];
5252 return YES;
5253 }

5255 [self executeCoreCommandByName:"ToggleItalic"];
5256 return YES;

5262- (BOOL)performKeyEquivalent:(NSEvent *)event
5263{
5264 // There's a chance that responding to this event will run a nested event loop, and
5265 // fetching a new event might release the old one. Retaining and then autoreleasing
5266 // the current event prevents that from causing a problem inside WebKit or AppKit code.
5267 retainPtr(event).autorelease();
5268
5269 BOOL eventWasSentToWebCore = (_private->keyDownEvent == event);
5270 BOOL ret = NO;
5271
5272 _private->keyDownEvent = event;
5273
5274 [self retain];
5275
5276 // Pass command-key combos through WebCore if there is a key binding available for
5277 // this event. This lets web pages have a crack at intercepting command-modified keypresses.
5278 // But don't do it if we have already handled the event.
5279 // Pressing Esc results in a fake event being sent - don't pass it to WebCore.
5280 if (!eventWasSentToWebCore && event == [NSApp currentEvent] && self == [[self window] firstResponder])
5281 if (auto* frame = core([self _frame]))
5282 ret = frame->eventHandler().keyEvent(event);
5283
5284 if (ret) {
5285#if PLATFORM(MAC)
5286 [NSCursor setHiddenUntilMouseMoves:YES];
5287#endif
5288 } else
5289 ret = [self _handleStyleKeyEquivalent:event] || [super performKeyEquivalent:event];
5290
5291 [self release];
5292
5293 return ret;
5294}

5963- (void)_executeSavedKeypressCommands
5964{
5965 auto* parameters = _private->interpretKeyEventsParameters;
5966 if (!parameters || parameters->event->keypressCommands().isEmpty())
5967 return;
5968
5969 // We could be called again if the execution of one command triggers a call to selectedRange.
5970 // In this case, the state is up to date, and we don't need to execute any more saved commands to return a result
5971 if (parameters->executingSavedKeypressCommands)
5972 return;
5973
5974 // Avoid an infinite loop that would occur if executing a command appended it to event->keypressCommands() again.
5975 bool wasSavingCommands = parameters->shouldSaveCommands;
5976 parameters->shouldSaveCommands = false;
5977 parameters->executingSavedKeypressCommands = true;
5978
5979 const Vector<WebCore::KeypressCommand>& commands = parameters->event->keypressCommands();
5980
5981 for (size_t i = 0; i < commands.size(); ++i) {
5982 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_BEGIN
5983 if (commands[i].commandName == "insertText:")
5984 [self insertText:commands[i].text];
5985 else if (commands[i].commandName == "noop:")
5986 ; // Do nothing. This case can be removed once <rdar://problem/9025012> is fixed.
5987 else
5988 [self doCommandBySelector:NSSelectorFromString(commands[i].commandName)];
5989 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_END
5990 }
5991 parameters->event->keypressCommands().clear();
5992 parameters->shouldSaveCommands = wasSavingCommands;
5993 parameters->executingSavedKeypressCommands = false;
5994}

5998- (BOOL)_interpretKeyEvent:(NakedPtr<WebCore::KeyboardEvent>)event savingCommands:(BOOL)savingCommands
5999{
6000 ASSERT(core([self _frame]) == downcast<WebCore::Node>(event->target())->document().frame());
6001 ASSERT(!savingCommands || event->keypressCommands().isEmpty()); // Save commands once for each event.
6002
6003 WebHTMLViewInterpretKeyEventsParameters parameters;
6004 parameters.eventInterpretationHadSideEffects = false;
6005 parameters.shouldSaveCommands = savingCommands;
6006 parameters.executingSavedKeypressCommands = false;
6007 // If we're intercepting the initial IM call we assume that the IM has consumed the event,
6008 // and only change this assumption if one of the NSTextInput/Responder callbacks is used.
6009 // We assume the IM will *not* consume hotkey sequences
6010 parameters.consumedByIM = savingCommands && !event->metaKey();
6011
6012 auto* platformEvent = event->underlyingPlatformEvent();
6013 if (!platformEvent)
6014 return NO;
6015
6016 NSEvent *macEvent = platformEvent->macEvent();
6017 if ([macEvent type] == NSEventTypeKeyDown && [_private->completionController filterKeyDown:macEvent])
6018 return YES;
6019
6020 if ([macEvent type] == NSEventTypeFlagsChanged)
6021 return NO;
6022
6023 parameters.event = event;
6024 _private->interpretKeyEventsParameters = &parameters;
6025 const Vector<WebCore::KeypressCommand>& commands = event->keypressCommands();
6026
6027 if (savingCommands) {
6028 // AppKit will respond with a series of NSTextInput protocol method calls. There are three groups that we heuristically differentiate:
6029 // 1. Key Bindings. Only doCommandBySelector: and insertText: calls will be made, which we save in the event for execution
6030 // after DOM dispatch. This is safe, because neither returns a result, so there is no branching on AppKit side.
6031 // 2. Plain text input. Here as well, we need to dispatch DOM events prior to inserting text, so we save the insertText: command.
6032 // 3. Input method processing. An IM can make any NSTextInput calls, and can base its decisions on results it gets, so we must
6033 // execute the calls immediately. DOM events like keydown are tweaked to have keyCode of 229, and canceling them has no effect.
6034 // Unfortunately, there is no real difference between plain text input and IM processing - for example, AppKit queries hasMarkedText
6035 // when typing with U.S. keyboard, and inserts marked text for dead keys.
6036 [self interpretKeyEvents:@[macEvent]];
6037 } else {
6038 // Are there commands that could just cause text insertion if executed via Editor?
6039 // WebKit doesn't have enough information about mode to decide how they should be treated, so we leave it upon WebCore
6040 // to either handle them immediately (e.g. Tab that changes focus) or let a keypress event be generated
6041 // (e.g. Tab that inserts a Tab character, or Enter).
6042 bool haveTextInsertionCommands = false;
6043 for (size_t i = 0; i < commands.size(); ++i) {
6044 if ([self coreCommandBySelector:NSSelectorFromString(commands[i].commandName)].isTextInsertion())
6045 haveTextInsertionCommands = true;
6046 }
6047 // If there are no text insertion commands, default keydown handler is the right time to execute the commands.
6048 // Keypress (Char event) handler is the latest opportunity to execute.
6049 if (!haveTextInsertionCommands || platformEvent->type() == WebCore::PlatformEvent::Char)
6050 [self _executeSavedKeypressCommands];
6051 }
6052 _private->interpretKeyEventsParameters = nullptr;
6053
6054 // An input method may make several actions per keypress. For example, pressing Return with Korean IM both confirms it and sends a newline.
6055 // IM-like actions are handled immediately (so parameters.eventInterpretationHadSideEffects is true), but there are saved commands that
6056 // should be handled like normal text input after DOM event dispatch.
6057 if (!event->keypressCommands().isEmpty())
6058 return NO;
6059
6060 // An input method may consume an event and not tell us (e.g. when displaying a candidate window),
6061 // in which case we should not bubble the event up the DOM.
6062 if (parameters.consumedByIM)
6063 return YES;
6064
6065 // If we have already executed all commands, don't do it again.
6066 return parameters.eventInterpretationHadSideEffects;
6067}
6068
6069#endif // PLATFORM(MAC)

6071#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
6072
6073- (BOOL)_handleEditingKeyEvent:(WebCore::KeyboardEvent *)wcEvent
6074{
6075 // Use the isEditable state to determine whether or not to process tab key events.
6076 // The idea here is that isEditable will be NO when this WebView is being used
6077 // in a browser, and we desire the behavior where tab moves to the next element
6078 // in tab order. If isEditable is YES, it is likely that the WebView is being
6079 // embedded as the whole view, as in Mail, and tabs should input tabs as expected
6080 // in a text editor.
6081
6082 if (auto* platformEvent = wcEvent->underlyingPlatformEvent()) {
6083 WebEvent *event = platformEvent->event();
6084 if (event.keyboardFlags & WebEventKeyboardInputModifierFlagsChanged)
6085 return NO;
6086
6087 WebView *webView = [self _webView];
6088 if (!webView.isEditable && event.isTabKey)
6089 return NO;
6090
6091 bool isCharEvent = platformEvent->type() == WebCore::PlatformKeyboardEvent::Char;
6092
6093 if (!isCharEvent && [webView._UIKitDelegateForwarder handleKeyTextCommandForCurrentEvent])
6094 return YES;
6095 if (isCharEvent && [webView._UIKitDelegateForwarder handleKeyAppCommandForCurrentEvent])
6096 return YES;
6097
6098 NSString *s = [event characters];
6099 if (!s.length)
6100 return NO;
6101 switch ([s characterAtIndex:0]) {
6102 case NSBackspaceCharacter:
6103 case NSDeleteCharacter:
6104 [[webView _UIKitDelegateForwarder] deleteFromInputWithFlags:event.keyboardFlags];
6105 return YES;
6106 case NSEnterCharacter:
6107 case NSCarriageReturnCharacter:
6108 if (isCharEvent) {
6109 // Map \r from HW keyboard to \n to match the behavior of the soft keyboard.
6110 [[webView _UIKitDelegateForwarder] addInputString:@"\n" withFlags:0];
6111 return YES;
6112 }
6113 break;
6114 default:
6115 if (isCharEvent) {
6116 [[webView _UIKitDelegateForwarder] addInputString:event.characters withFlags:event.keyboardFlags];
6117 return YES;
6118 }
6119 }
6120 }
6121 return NO;
6122}

6172 auto hostingView = adoptNS([[WebLayerHostingFlippedView alloc] initWithFrame:[self bounds]]);

6504static void extractUnderlines(NSAttributedString *string, Vector<WebCore::CompositionUnderline>& result)
6505{
6506 int length = [[string string] length];
6507
6508 int i = 0;
6509 while (i < length) {
6510 NSRange range;
6511 NSDictionary *attrs = [string attributesAtIndex:i longestEffectiveRange:&range inRange:NSMakeRange(i, length - i)];
6512
6513 if (NSNumber *style = [attrs objectForKey:NSUnderlineStyleAttributeName]) {
6514 WebCore::Color color = WebCore::Color::black;
6515 auto compositionUnderlineColor = WebCore::CompositionUnderlineColor::TextColor;
6516 if (NSColor *colorAttr = [attrs objectForKey:NSUnderlineColorAttributeName]) {
6517 color = WebCore::colorFromNSColor(colorAttr);
6518 compositionUnderlineColor = WebCore::CompositionUnderlineColor::GivenColor;
6519 }
6520 result.append(WebCore::CompositionUnderline(range.location, NSMaxRange(range), compositionUnderlineColor, color, [style intValue] > 1));
6521 }
6522
6523 i = range.location + range.length;
6524 }
6525}

6530- (void)setMarkedText:(id)string selectedRange:(NSRange)newSelRange
6531ALLOW_DEPRECATED_IMPLEMENTATIONS_END
6532{
6533 [self _executeSavedKeypressCommands];
6534
6535#if PLATFORM(MAC)
6536 BOOL isAttributedString = [string isKindOfClass:[NSAttributedString class]];
6537 ASSERT(isAttributedString || [string isKindOfClass:[NSString class]]);
6538
6539 LOG(TextInput, "setMarkedText:\"%@\" selectedRange:(%u, %u)", isAttributedString ? [string string] : string, newSelRange.location, newSelRange.length);
6540#endif
6541
6542 // Use pointer to get parameters passed to us by the caller of interpretKeyEvents.
6543 auto* parameters = _private->interpretKeyEventsParameters;
6544
6545 if (parameters) {
6546 parameters->eventInterpretationHadSideEffects = true;
6547 parameters->consumedByIM = false;
6548 }
6549
6550 auto* coreFrame = core([self _frame]);
6551 if (!coreFrame)
6552 return;
6553
6554 if (![self _isEditable])
6555 return;
6556
6557 Vector<WebCore::CompositionUnderline> underlines;
6558 NSString *text;
6559 NSRange replacementRange = { NSNotFound, 0 };
6560
6561#if PLATFORM(MAC)
6562 if (isAttributedString) {
6563 // FIXME: We ignore most attributes from the string, so an input method cannot specify e.g. a font or a glyph variation.
6564 text = [string string];
6565 NSString *rangeString = [string attribute:NSTextInputReplacementRangeAttributeName atIndex:0 longestEffectiveRange:0 inRange:NSMakeRange(0, [text length])];
6566 LOG(TextInput, " ReplacementRange: %@", rangeString);
6567 // The AppKit adds a 'secret' property to the string that contains the replacement range.
6568 // The replacement range is the range of the text that should be replaced with the new string.
6569 if (rangeString)
6570 replacementRange = NSRangeFromString(rangeString);
6571
6572 extractUnderlines(string, underlines);
6573 } else {
6574 text = string;
6575 underlines.append(WebCore::CompositionUnderline(0, [text length], WebCore::CompositionUnderlineColor::TextColor, WebCore::Color::black, false));
6576 }
6577#else
6578 text = string;
6579#endif
6580
6581 if (replacementRange.location != NSNotFound)
6582 [[self _frame] _selectNSRange:replacementRange];
6583
6584 coreFrame->editor().setComposition(text, underlines, { }, newSelRange.location, NSMaxRange(newSelRange));
6585}

6587ALLOW_DEPRECATED_IMPLEMENTATIONS_BEGIN
6588- (void)doCommandBySelector:(SEL)selector
6589ALLOW_DEPRECATED_IMPLEMENTATIONS_END
6590{
6591 LOG(TextInput, "doCommandBySelector:\"%s\"", sel_getName(selector));
6592
6593 // Use pointer to get parameters passed to us by the caller of interpretKeyEvents.
6594 // The same call to interpretKeyEvents can do more than one command.
6595 auto* parameters = _private->interpretKeyEventsParameters;
6596 if (parameters)
6597 parameters->consumedByIM = false;
6598
6599 auto* event = parameters ? parameters->event : 0;
6600 bool shouldSaveCommand = parameters && parameters->shouldSaveCommands;
6601
6602 // As in insertText:, we assume that the call comes from an input method if there is marked text.
6603 RefPtr<WebCore::Frame> coreFrame = core([self _frame]);
6604 bool isFromInputMethod = coreFrame && coreFrame->editor().hasComposition();
6605
6606 if (event && shouldSaveCommand && !isFromInputMethod)
6607 event->keypressCommands().append(WebCore::KeypressCommand(NSStringFromSelector(selector)));
6608 else {
6609 // Make sure that only direct calls to doCommandBySelector: see the parameters by setting to 0.
6610 _private->interpretKeyEventsParameters = 0;
6611
6612 bool eventWasHandled;
6613
6614 WebView *webView = [self _webView];
6615 if ([[webView _editingDelegateForwarder] webView:webView doCommandBySelector:selector])
6616 eventWasHandled = true;
6617 else {
6618 WebCore::Editor::Command command = [self coreCommandBySelector:selector];
6619 if (command.isSupported())
6620 eventWasHandled = command.execute(event);
6621 else {
6622#if PLATFORM(MAC)
6623 // If WebKit does not support this command, we need to pass the selector to super.
6624 _private->selectorForDoCommandBySelector = selector;
6625
6626 // The sink does two things: 1) Tells us if the responder went unhandled, and
6627 // 2) prevents any NSBeep; we don't ever want to beep here.
6628 auto sink = adoptNS([[WebResponderChainSink alloc] initWithResponderChain:self]);
6629 [super doCommandBySelector:selector];
6630 eventWasHandled = ![sink receivedUnhandledCommand];
6631 [sink detach];
6632
6633 _private->selectorForDoCommandBySelector = 0;
6634#else
6635 eventWasHandled = false;
6636#endif
6637 }
6638 }
6639
6640 if (parameters)
6641 parameters->eventInterpretationHadSideEffects |= eventWasHandled;
6642
6643 _private->interpretKeyEventsParameters = parameters;
6644 }
6645}

6647ALLOW_DEPRECATED_IMPLEMENTATIONS_BEGIN
6648- (void)insertText:(id)string
6649ALLOW_DEPRECATED_IMPLEMENTATIONS_END
6650{
6651#if PLATFORM(MAC)
6652 BOOL isAttributedString = [string isKindOfClass:[NSAttributedString class]];
6653 ASSERT(isAttributedString || [string isKindOfClass:[NSString class]]);
6654
6655 LOG(TextInput, "insertText:\"%@\"", isAttributedString ? [string string] : string);
6656#endif
6657
6658 auto* parameters = _private->interpretKeyEventsParameters;
6659 if (parameters)
6660 parameters->consumedByIM = false;
6661
6662 RefPtr<WebCore::Frame> coreFrame = core([self _frame]);
6663 NSString *text;
6664 NSRange replacementRange = { NSNotFound, 0 };
6665 bool isFromInputMethod = coreFrame && coreFrame->editor().hasComposition();
6666#if USE(INSERTION_UNDO_GROUPING)
6667 bool registerUndoGroup = false;
6668#endif
6669
6670 Vector<WebCore::DictationAlternative> dictationAlternativeLocations;
6671#if PLATFORM(MAC)
6672 if (isAttributedString) {
6673 Vector<WebCore::TextAlternativeWithRange> textAlternatives;
6674 collectDictationTextAlternatives(string, textAlternatives);
6675 if (!textAlternatives.isEmpty())
6676 [[self _webView] _getWebCoreDictationAlternatives:dictationAlternativeLocations fromTextAlternatives:textAlternatives];
6677 registerUndoGroup = WebCore::shouldRegisterInsertionUndoGroup(string);
6678 // FIXME: We ignore most attributes from the string, so for example inserting from Character Palette loses font and glyph variation data.
6679 // It does not look like any input methods ever use insertText: with attributes other than NSTextInputReplacementRangeAttributeName.
6680 text = [string string];
6681 NSString *rangeString = [string attribute:NSTextInputReplacementRangeAttributeName atIndex:0 longestEffectiveRange:0 inRange:NSMakeRange(0, [text length])];
6682 LOG(TextInput, " ReplacementRange: %@", rangeString);
6683 if (rangeString) {
6684 replacementRange = NSRangeFromString(rangeString);
6685 isFromInputMethod = true;
6686 }
6687 } else
6688#endif
6689 text = string;
6690
6691 auto* event = parameters ? parameters->event : 0;
6692
6693 // insertText can be called for several reasons:
6694 // - If it's from normal key event processing (including key bindings), we may need to save the action to perform it later.
6695 // - If it's from an input method, then we should insert the text now. We assume it's from the input method if we have marked text.
6696 // FIXME: In theory, this could be wrong for some input methods, so we should try to find another way to determine if the call is from the input method.
6697 // - If it's sent outside of keyboard event processing (e.g. from Character Viewer, or when confirming an inline input area with a mouse),
6698 // then we also execute it immediately, as there will be no other chance.
6699 bool shouldSaveCommand = parameters && parameters->shouldSaveCommands;
6700 if (event && shouldSaveCommand && !isFromInputMethod) {
6701 event->keypressCommands().append(WebCore::KeypressCommand("insertText:", text));
6702 return;
6703 }
6704
6705 if (!coreFrame || !coreFrame->editor().canEdit())
6706 return;
6707
6708 BOOL needToRemoveSoftSpace = NO;
6709#if PLATFORM(MAC)
6710 if (_private->softSpaceRange.location != NSNotFound && (replacementRange.location == NSMaxRange(_private->softSpaceRange) || replacementRange.location == NSNotFound) && !replacementRange.length && [[NSSpellChecker sharedSpellChecker] deletesAutospaceBeforeString:text language:nil]) {
6711 replacementRange = _private->softSpaceRange;
6712 needToRemoveSoftSpace = YES;
6713 }
6714 _private->softSpaceRange = NSMakeRange(NSNotFound, 0);
6715#endif
6716
6717 bool replacesText = false;
6718 if (replacementRange.location != NSNotFound) {
6719 WebRangeIsRelativeTo rangeIsRelativeTo = needToRemoveSoftSpace ? WebRangeIsRelativeTo::Paragraph : WebRangeIsRelativeTo::EditableRoot;
6720 if (auto domRange = [[self _frame] _convertToDOMRange:replacementRange rangeIsRelativeTo:rangeIsRelativeTo]) {
6721 WebCore::IgnoreSelectionChangeForScope selectionChange { *coreFrame };
6722 coreFrame->selection().setSelection(WebCore::VisibleSelection(*domRange));
6723 replacesText = replacementRange.length;
6724 }
6725 }
6726
6727 bool eventHandled = false;
6728 String eventText = text;
6729 eventText.replace(NSBackTabCharacter, NSTabCharacter); // same thing is done in KeyEventMac.mm in WebCore
6730 if (!coreFrame->editor().hasComposition()) {
6731 // An insertText: might be handled by other responders in the chain if we don't handle it.
6732 // One example is space bar that results in scrolling down the page.
6733
6734 if (!dictationAlternativeLocations.isEmpty())
6735 eventHandled = coreFrame->editor().insertDictatedText(eventText, dictationAlternativeLocations, event);
6736 else
6737 eventHandled = coreFrame->editor().insertText(eventText, event, replacesText ? WebCore::TextEventInputAutocompletion : WebCore::TextEventInputKeyboard);
6738
6739#if USE(INSERTION_UNDO_GROUPING)
6740 if (registerUndoGroup)
6741 WebCore::registerInsertionUndoGroupingWithUndoManager([[self _webView] undoManager]);
6742#endif
6743 } else {
6744 eventHandled = true;
6745 coreFrame->editor().confirmComposition(eventText);
6746 }
6747
6748 if (parameters)
6749 parameters->eventInterpretationHadSideEffects |= eventHandled;
6750}

6856
6857static CGImageRef imageFromRect(WebCore::Frame* frame, CGRect rect)
6858{
6859 auto* page = frame->page();
6860 if (!page)
6861 return nil;
6862 WAKView* documentView = frame->view()->documentView();
6863 if (!documentView)
6864 return nil;
6865 if (![documentView isKindOfClass:[WebHTMLView class]])
6866 return nil;
6867
6868 WebHTMLView *view = (WebHTMLView *)documentView;
6869
6870 OptionSet<WebCore::PaintBehavior> oldPaintBehavior = frame->view()->paintBehavior();
6871 frame->view()->setPaintBehavior(oldPaintBehavior | WebCore::PaintBehavior::FlattenCompositingLayers | WebCore::PaintBehavior::Snapshotting);
6872
6873 BEGIN_BLOCK_OBJC_EXCEPTIONS
6874
6875 CGRect bounds = [view bounds];
6876
6877 float scale = page->pageScaleFactor() * page->deviceScaleFactor();
6878
6879 // Round image rect size in window coordinate space to avoid pixel cracks at HiDPI (4622794)
6880 rect = [view convertRect:rect toView:nil];
6881 rect.size.height = roundf(rect.size.height);
6882 rect.size.width = roundf(rect.size.width);
6883 rect = [view convertRect:rect fromView:nil];
6884 if (rect.size.width == 0 || rect.size.height == 0)
6885 return nil;
6886
6887 size_t width = static_cast<size_t>(rect.size.width * scale);
6888 size_t height = static_cast<size_t>(rect.size.height * scale);
6889 size_t bitsPerComponent = 8;
6890 size_t bitsPerPixel = 4 * bitsPerComponent;
6891 size_t bytesPerRow = ((bitsPerPixel + 7) / 8) * width;
6892 RetainPtr<CGContextRef> context = adoptCF(CGBitmapContextCreate(NULL, width, height, bitsPerComponent, bytesPerRow, WebCore::sRGBColorSpaceRef(), kCGImageAlphaPremultipliedLast));
6893 if (!context)
6894 return nil;
6895
6896 CGContextRef oldContext = WKGetCurrentGraphicsContext();
6897 CGContextRef contextRef = context.get();
6898 WKSetCurrentGraphicsContext(contextRef);
6899
6900 CGContextClearRect(contextRef, CGRectMake(0, 0, width, height));
6901 CGContextSaveGState(contextRef);
6902 CGContextScaleCTM(contextRef, scale, scale);
6903 CGContextSetBaseCTM(contextRef, CGAffineTransformMakeScale(scale, scale));
6904 CGContextTranslateCTM(contextRef, bounds.origin.x - rect.origin.x, bounds.origin.y - rect.origin.y);
6905
6906 [view drawSingleRect:rect];
6907
6908 CGContextRestoreGState(contextRef);
6909
6910 RetainPtr<CGImageRef> resultImage = adoptCF(CGBitmapContextCreateImage(contextRef));
6911
6912 WKSetCurrentGraphicsContext(oldContext);
6913 frame->view()->setPaintBehavior(oldPaintBehavior);
6914
6915 return resultImage.autorelease();
6916
6917 END_BLOCK_OBJC_EXCEPTIONS
6918
6919 frame->view()->setPaintBehavior(oldPaintBehavior);
6920 return nil;
